---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HeroCanvasNeural from '../components/hero/HeroCanvasNeural.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Rohit Burani" description="Engineering, management, and the commitment to sustainable systems behind Gekro Lab.">
  <HeroCanvasNeural />
  
  <main class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-32 space-y-32">
    <!-- Section 1: Opening Header -->
    <header class="space-y-12">
      <div class="space-y-6 max-w-2xl">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-accent">Biography // Logic_01</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-8xl font-heading font-medium text-text-primary tracking-tighter">
          Systems at scale.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-text-primary leading-relaxed">
          I’ve always been obsessed with how things connect at a fundamental level. My education—an engineering bachelors followed by a Masters in Management—trained me to look past the surface of technology to the operational logic and human impact beneath. That combination — analytical rigour meeting operational reality — is the lens I bring to everything built in this lab.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="aspect-video bg-bg-elevated rounded-2xl border border-border overflow-hidden relative flex items-center justify-center p-12">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-tr from-accent/5 to-transparent"></div>
          
          <!-- Systems Efficiency / Sustainability Hybrid SVG -->
          <svg width="400" height="200" viewBox="0 0 400 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-full max-w-md opacity-40">
            <circle cx="200" cy="100" r="60" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="4 4" />
            <path d="M140 100C140 66.8629 166.863 40 200 40C233.137 40 260 66.8629 260 100" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <path d="M140 100L120 100M260 100L280 100M200 40L200 20" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" />
            
            <rect x="170" y="80" width="60" height="40" stroke="var(--color-text-primary)" stroke-width="1" />
            <path d="M185 100H215" stroke="var(--color-text-muted)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="2 2" />
            
            <text x="200" y="145" text-anchor="middle" class="fill-accent font-mono text-[7px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">Efficiency_Architecture // System_Optimization</text>
            <text x="200" y="165" text-anchor="middle" class="fill-text-muted font-mono text-[5px] uppercase">Gekro_System_Core: 03-24 [Synced]</text>
          </svg>
          
          <span class="absolute bottom-8 left-8 text-[10px] font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-widest opacity-50">Log_Type: Efficiency_Schematic</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Section 2: The Lab -->
    <section class="max-w-2xl space-y-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-text-primary">The Lab</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg text-text-secondary">
        <p>
          Gekro is my workshop. It’s where I take technical concepts and put them through the stress of actual implementation. While my professional life is spent navigating the complexities of large, regulated organizations, my personal time is dedicated to building, breaking, and documenting experiments in the lab.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Technical Philosophy -->
    <section class="space-y-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-text-primary">Technical Philosophy</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <span class="text-accent font-mono text-sm underline decoration-2 underline-offset-8">01 / Sovereignty</span>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Privacy isn't a feature; it's a foundation. Cybersecurity is the bedrock of trust, building systems where you own the weights, the data, and the hardware—ensuring our digital footprints remain our own.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <span class="text-accent font-mono text-sm underline decoration-2 underline-offset-8">02 / Sustainability</span>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Efficiency is the ultimate elegance. The reduction of waste is as important as speed. I prioritize systems that optimize for energy consumption and resource longevity—because building things that last is the only way forward.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <span class="text-accent font-mono text-sm underline decoration-2 underline-offset-8">03 / Empirical</span>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            In an era of AI hype, I value the empirical. Every project here is backed by logs, telemetry, and functional code. If it doesn't run in the lab, it doesn't belong on the site. Proof over promise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Scale Experience -->
    <section class="max-w-2xl space-y-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-text-primary">Built for Depth</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg text-text-secondary">
        <p>
          The experiments you see here aren't academic exercises. They are informed by years of solving operational problems inside complex, scale-heavy environments. There is a specific kind of intuition that comes from seeing how things actually fail in production—the edge cases that theory misses and the robustness required when systems are mission-critical. I bring that production-first mindset into every local LLM or autonomous home automation experiment I run.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Beyond the Lab -->
    <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-text-primary">Beyond the Lab</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg text-text-secondary">
          <p>
            Outside the terminal, I'm most at home in the backcountry — camping with family, hiking trails that have no cell signal, driving electric wherever possible.
          </p>
          <p>
            That same belief in sustainable systems that drives the lab work carries into how I live — green energy, minimal waste, long-term thinking over short-term convenience.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="aspect-square bg-bg-elevated rounded-2xl border border-border p-12 relative flex items-center justify-center">
        <!-- Natural Flow / Sustainable Systems SVG -->
        <svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-full opacity-30">
          <path d="M40 150Q70 140 100 150T160 150" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" />
          <path d="M40 130Q70 120 100 130T160 130" stroke="var(--color-text-muted)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="2 2" />
          <circle cx="100" cy="80" r="20" stroke="var(--color-text-primary)" stroke-width="1" />
          <path d="M100 60L100 30" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1" />
          <text x="100" y="175" text-anchor="middle" class="fill-text-muted font-mono text-[8px] uppercase tracking-widest">Natural_Flow // Systems_Sync</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 6: Closing -->
    <footer class="pt-32 space-y-12">
      <div class="max-w-xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-text-primary italic border-l-2 border-accent pl-8 py-2">
          If something here resonates, reach out.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pt-12 border-t border-border-subtle flex justify-between items-center">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase">EST. 2024 // UPDATED 2026 // ROHIT BURANI</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="group flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-mono text-accent hover:text-white transition-colors">
          Get in touch 
          <span class="group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
